at depend very heavily on societal attitudes, although often via causal webs rather </span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> through simple one to one cause and effect. It is not coincidence that the more prudish western countries, of which the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> one, have body atti</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">tude related outcomes that are appalling compared to those countries with more wholesome attitudes. For example compared to Denmark, a teenager in the USA is several times more likely to have an abortion, about ten times more likely to become pregnant, and</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> several tens of times more likely to catch a sexually transmitted infection. That pattern repeats for every international comparison that we have looked at and for every indicator.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Sans'; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Objectives of the BBC</span></h2><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">The primary objective of the BBC must be to provide </span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">reliable, objective, and accurate information and educations to the public, free from any commercial or political pressures. By doing so it also fulfils the important role of helping to keep the commercial broadcasters honest.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Sans'; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Current performance</span></h2><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">The curre</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">nt charter and guidelines have proved inadequate to ensure honest programme making and indeed the guidelines have actually contributed to the problem. An example will suffice to demonstrate the problem and unfortunately it is far from unique.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Andrew Marr's</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> History of the World was an otherwise excellent series but there were at least six scenes, six aspects of history, where the costumes were complete fiction. We made a complaint to the BBC. They acknowledged that we were correct and said that it was for co</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">mmercial reasons.Â  The censorship was made worse because there was no way for anyone without specialist knowledge to know that the programme had been censored to the point of dishonesty. Issues arising:</span></li></ol><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Systematic and deliberate falsification of history.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">N</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">o consideration of the social harm done by prudery.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">No consideration of the harm done to the reputation of the BBC for honesty and accuracy.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">No transparency. It is impossible to complain about censorship if it is not known about.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">No accountability. There c</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">an be no accountability without transparency.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Sans'; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Content classification</span></h2><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">There is a need to regulate what is shown and in our opinion there should be four categories of material:</span></li></ol><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Innocuous for most people. Make generally available.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">May offend some people. The </span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">viewer should be informed so that they have the option to watch something else or to turn off. NB the viewer must be informed, not warned. The latter word should be reserved for use in the context of harm.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">There is objective evidence that the harm outweigh</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">s the benefit for some categories of viewer. Depending on the severity then restricting access may be justified.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Significant harm will result from showing the material. Don't show it.</span></li></ol><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">The important principle is that decisions on programme content and how i</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">t is made available must be made according to the objective evidence of harm and benefit, not according to perceived popular prejudice, who shouts </span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">loudest,</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> or commercial considerations. The welfare of children and young people is far too important for myth</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> and prejudice to play any part in decision making.</span></li></ol><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Sans'; font-size:14pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">A new charter</span></h2><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 14pt; padding-left:0.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Accordingly we feel that the charter must require:</span></li></ol><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Honesty and accuracy;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Transparency and accountability;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Restrictions on content according to objective evidence of harm and benefit,</span><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt"> not perceived popular prejudice or who shouts loudest;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; margin:2.85pt 0pt 2.85pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">Commercial considerations must be subordinate to the above.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:2.85pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:2.85pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>